title.narrative: Competitive Value Chains for Jobs and Economic Transformation Project

description.narrative: The project development objectives are to: (i) improve the competitiveness of supported value chains, (ii) increase access to finance for underserved farmers and firms, and (iii) in case of an Eligible Crisis or Emergency, respond promptly and effectively to it.

condition.narrative: Schedule II. Section I.A. 1. (a): The Recipient shall no later than three (3) months after the Effective Date, establish andmaintain throughout Project implementation, a Project steering committee (“Project Steering Committee” or “PSC”) for the Project,with a composition, mandate and resources satisfactory to the Association.

Schedule II. Section I.A. 2. (a): No later than twelve (12) months after the Effective Date, the Project Coordination Unit shalltake over the overall Project coordination, monitoring and evaluation, fiduciary, environmental and social aspects of the Project,all in accordance with the provisions of the Financing Agreement and the Project Implementation Manual (PIM).

Schedule II. Section I.A. 2. (a): The Recipient shall, as a transitional measure, maintain until no later than twelve (12) monthsafter the Effective Date: (i) a Project coordinator within the Prime Minister's office to be responsible for overall Projectcoordination and monitoring and evaluation; and (ii) an implementation unit within FIRCA with functions, staffing and resourcessatisfactory to the Association, to be responsible for fiduciary, environmental and social aspects of the Project.

Schedule II. Section I.A. 2. (b): The Recipient shall maintain throughout Project implementation a Project coordination unit(“Project Coordination Unit” or “PCU”) headed by a Project coordinator, at the Prime Minister's Office, with adequate resources andstaff, to be recruited no later than twelve (12) months after the Effective Date, including: (i) a procurement specialist; (ii) anassistant procurement specialist; (iii) a financial management specialist; (iv) an accountant; (v) an environmental safeguardspecialist, (vi) a social safeguards specialist,(vii) a monitoring and evaluation specialist, (viii) a communications specialistand (ix) competitiveness specialists, all to be recruited through either government appointment or a competitive basis and withqualifications, experience and terms of reference satisfactory to the Association.

Schedule II. Section IV. A.1: Within three (3) months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall:(a) sign a protocol with IGFto include the Project in the scope of its work to carry out internal audit functions for the Project; (b) appoint and thereaftermaintain during Project implementation, an accountant dedicated to the Project, with qualifications, experience and under terms ofreference acceptable to the Association; and, (c) update the accounting software for the Project in a manner satisfactory to theAssociation.

Schedule II. Section IV. A.2: Within six (6) months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall recruit, and thereafter maintainduring Project implementation, an independent external auditor for the Project, with qualifications, experience and under terms ofreference acceptable to the Association.
